Caroline Meade, how can you permit your husband to conduct this

00:42:42,96 --> 00:42:44,64
this slave auction?

00:42:44,67 --> 00:42:47,26
Dolly Merriwether, how dare you criticize me.

00:42:47,68 --> 00:42:49,35
Melanie Wilkes told the doctor

00:42:49,39 --> 00:42:52,22
that if it's for the benefit of the cause, it's quite all right.

00:42:52,26 --> 00:42:53,52
She did.

00:42:53,56 --> 00:42:56,56
Oh dear, oh dear. Where are my smelling salts?

00:42:56,98 --> 00:42:58,23
I think I shall faint.

00:42:58,27 --> 00:43:00,73
Don't you dare faint, Pittypat Hamilton.

00:43:00,77 --> 00:43:03,36
If Melanie says it's all right, it is all right.

00:43:04,69 --> 00:43:07,49
Come, gentlemen, do I hear your bids? Make your offers.

00:43:08,36 --> 00:43:10,07
Don't be bashful, gentlemen.

00:43:10,87 --> 00:43:14,83
Twenty dollars, $20 for Miss Maybelle Merriwether.

00:43:14,87 --> 00:43:17,24
Twenty-five dollars for Miss Fanny Elsing.

00:43:17,27 --> 00:43:19,33
Only $25 to give your

00:43:19,38 --> 00:43:21,46
One hundred and fifty dollars in gold.

00:43:22,09 --> 00:43:23,34
For what lady, sir?

00:43:23,38 --> 00:43:25,30
For Mrs. Charles Hamilton.

00:43:28,18 --> 00:43:29,26
For whom, sir?

00:43:29,68 --> 00:43:31,43
Mrs. Charles Hamilton.

00:43:31,47 --> 00:43:33,72
Mrs. Hamilton is in mourning, Captain Butler

00:43:33,76 --> 00:43:36,52
but I'm sure any of our Atlanta belles would be proud to

00:43:36,56 --> 00:43:40,06
Dr. Meade, I said Mrs. Charles Hamilton.

00:43:40,77 --> 00:43:43,23
She will not consider it, sir.

00:43:43,27 --> 00:43:44,57
Oh yes, I will.

00:43:56,87 --> 00:44:00,08
Choose your partners for the Virginia reel.

00:44:01,17 --> 00:44:03,25
We've sort of shocked the Confederacy.

00:44:03,29 --> 00:44:04,96
It's a bit like blockade-running, isn't it?

00:44:05,30 --> 00:44:06,42
It's worse.

00:44:06,46 --> 00:44:08,42
But I expect a very fancy profit out of it.

00:44:08,47 --> 00:44:10,22
I don't care what you expect or what they think.

00:44:10,26 --> 00:44:11,84
I'm going to dance and dance.

00:44:11,89 --> 00:44:14,89
Tonight I wouldn't mind dancing with Abe LincoIn himself.

00:44:46,80 --> 00:44:49,42
Another dance and my reputation will be lost forever.

00:44:49,47 --> 00:44:51,63
With enough courage, you can do without a reputation.

00:44:51,68 --> 00:44:53,76
Oh, you do talk scandalous.

00:45:01,77 --> 00:45:04,23
You do waltz divinely, Captain Butler.

00:45:04,27 --> 00:45:08,15
Don't start flirting with me. I'm not one of your plantation beaux.

00:45:08,19 --> 00:45:10,49
I want more than flirting from you.

00:45:10,99 --> 00:45:12,28
What do you want?

00:45:13,07 --> 00:45:18,04
I'll tell you, Scarlett O'Hara, if you'll take that Southern belle simper off your face.

00:45:18,29 --> 00:45:19,83
Some day I want you to say to me

00:45:19,87 --> 00:45:22,66
the words I heard you say to Ashley Wilkes

00:45:23,08 --> 00:45:24,29
l love you.

00:45:24,79 --> 00:45:28,80
That's something you'll never hear from me, Captain Butler, as long as you live.

00:45:48,26 --> 00:45:51,50
How sweet, how kind.

00:45:51,86 --> 00:45:53,82
He is a thoughtful gentleman.

00:45:53,86 --> 00:46:00,17
Fiddle-dee-dee, why doesn't he say something about my sacrifice?

00:46:03,97 --> 00:46:07,63
Oh, the darling thing.

00:46:07,67 --> 00:46:09,10
Oh, Rhett, it's lovely, lovely.

00:46:09,14 --> 00:46:12,92
You didn't really bring it all the way from Paris just for me.

00:46:12,97 --> 00:46:16,49
Yes, I thought it was about time I got you out of that fake mourning.

00:46:16,53 --> 00:46:20,02
Next trip I'll bring you some green silk for a frock to match it.

00:46:20,05 --> 00:46:21,14
Oh, Rhett.

00:46:21,18 --> 00:46:27,02
It's my duty to our brave boys at the front to keep our girIs at home looking pretty.

00:46:27,05 --> 00:46:30,07
Oh, it's so long since I've had anything new.

00:46:40,28 --> 00:46:41,58
How do I look?

00:46:42,58 --> 00:46:44,16
Awful. Just awful.

00:46:44,87 --> 00:46:46,12
Why, what's the matter?

00:46:46,17 --> 00:46:47,42
This war has stopped being a joke

00:46:47,46 --> 00:46:50,67
when a girl like you doesn't know how to wear the latest fashion.

00:46:55,29 --> 00:46:58,59
Oh, Rhett, let me do it.

00:47:03,97 --> 00:47:07,06
But, Rhett, I don't know how I dare wear it.

00:47:07,98 --> 00:47:09,10
You will though.

00:47:09,14 --> 00:47:12,55
And another thing, those pantalettes.

00:47:12,57 --> 00:47:15,44
I don't know a woman in Paris that wears pantalettes anymore.

00:47:15,49 --> 00:47:16,70
Oh, what do they?

00:47:17,07 --> 00:47:19,24
You shouldn't talk about such things.

00:47:19,28 --> 00:47:20,32
You little hypocrite.

00:47:20,37 --> 00:47:23,04
You don't mind my knowing about them, just my talking.

00:47:23,08 --> 00:47:27,08
But, I really can't go on accepting gifts from you, though you are awfully kind.

00:47:27,11 --> 00:47:28,92
I'm not kind. I'm just tempting you.

00:47:28,96 --> 00:47:32,75
I never give anything without expecting something in return. I always get paid.

00:47:32,80 --> 00:47:35,26
If you think I'll marry you to pay for the bonnet, I won't.

00:47:35,30 --> 00:47:38,02
Don't flatter yourself. I'm not a marrying man.

00:47:38,68 --> 00:47:41,26
Well, I won't kiss you for it either.

00:47:51,56 --> 00:47:53,36
Open your eyes and look at me.

00:47:54,78 --> 00:47:56,74
No, I don't think I will kiss you

00:47:56,78 --> 00:47:58,53
although you need kissing badly.

00:47:58,57 --> 00:47:59,95
That's what's wrong with you.

00:47:59,99 --> 00:48:02,95
You should be kissed and often. And by someone who knows how.

00:48:02,99 --> 00:48:05,62
Oh, and I suppose you think you're the proper person.

00:48:05,66 --> 00:48:08,50
I might be, if the right moment ever came.

00:48:09,00 --> 00:48:11,75
You're a conceited, black-hearted varmint, Rhett Butler.

00:48:11,79 --> 00:48:14,46
And I don't know why I let you come and see me.

00:48:14,88 --> 00:48:16,55
I'll tell you why, Scarlett.

00:48:16,59 --> 00:48:18,84
Because I'm the only man over 16 and under 60

00:48:18,88 --> 00:48:20,55
who's around to show you a good time.

00:48:20,59 --> 00:48:23,85
But cheer up, the war can't last much longer.

00:48:23,89 --> 00:48:25,64
Oh really, Rhett? Why?

00:48:25,68 --> 00:48:28,85
There's a battle going on right now that ought to pretty well fix things

00:48:28,89 --> 00:48:29,94
one way or the other.

00:48:29,98 --> 00:48:32,06
Oh, Rhett. Is Ashley in it?

00:48:33,77 --> 00:48:37,03
You still haven't gotten the wooden-headed Mr. Wilkes out of your mind.

00:48:37,07 --> 00:48:38,53
Yes, I suppose he's in it.

00:48:38,57 --> 00:48:40,49
Oh, but tell me, Rhett, where is it?

00:48:40,86 --> 00:48:43,99
Some little town in Pennsylvania called Gettysburg.

00:50:04,95 --> 00:50:06,53
Here you is, Miss Melanie.

00:50:06,57 --> 00:50:09,28
They was fightin' for them so it just got tore in half.

00:50:09,58 --> 00:50:12,37
Scarlett, you look. The W's at the end.

00:50:16,29 --> 00:50:19,67
Wellman, Wendell, White, Whitner, Wilkins

00:50:20,30 --> 00:50:21,55
Williams, Woolsey, Workman.

00:50:21,59 --> 00:50:23,88
Scarlett, you've passed him.

00:50:24,47 --> 00:50:26,34
Oh, he isn't there.

00:50:26,39 --> 00:50:27,34
He isn't there.

00:50:27,39 --> 00:50:29,64
Ashley's safe. He isn't listed.

00:50:29,68 --> 00:50:31,89
Oh, he's safe, he's safe.

00:50:33,68 --> 00:50:37,69
Oh, Scarlett, you're so sweet to worry about Ashley like this for me.

00:50:45,20 --> 00:50:46,57
I must go to her.

00:50:48,16 --> 00:50:49,99
Don't, my dear, not here.

00:50:50,99 --> 00:50:52,29
Let's go home.

00:50:53,66 --> 00:50:55,33
Dr. Meade, not.

00:50:55,37 --> 00:50:58,08
Yes, our boy, Darcy.

00:50:58,88 --> 00:51:01,46
I was making these mittens for him.

00:51:02,17 --> 00:51:03,96
He won't need them now.

00:51:04,97 --> 00:51:08,93
Mother, I'm going to enlist. I'll show 'em. I'll kill all those Yankees.

00:51:08,97 --> 00:51:10,43
Phil Meade, you hush your mouth.

00:51:10,47 --> 00:51:12,72
Do you think it will help your mother to have you off getting shot too?

00:51:12,77 --> 00:51:14,56
I never heard of anything so silly.

00:51:17,27 --> 00:51:20,52
It's a black day, Scarlett. You haven't had bad news, have you?

00:51:20,56 --> 00:51:21,77
Ashley's safe.

00:51:22,07 --> 00:51:23,73
I'm glad, for Mrs. Wilkes' sake.

00:51:23,78 --> 00:51:25,32
But, Rhett, there are so many others.

00:51:25,36 --> 00:51:26,32
Many of your friends?

00:51:26,36 --> 00:51:30,03
Just about every family in the county. The Tarleton boys, Rhett, both of them.

00:51:30,07 --> 00:51:33,87
Yes, look at them. All these poor tragic people.

00:51:34,66 --> 00:51:38,17
The South's sinking to its knees. It'll never rise again.

00:51:38,96 --> 00:51:40,38
The cause.

00:51:40,67 --> 00:51:43,92
The cause of living in the past is dying right in front of us.

00:51:43,96 --> 00:51:45,92
I never heard you talk like that before.

00:51:45,96 --> 00:51:49,97
I'm angry. Waste always makes me angry. And that's what all this is, sheer waste.

00:51:52,39 --> 00:51:53,89
But don't you be downcast.

00:51:54,18 --> 00:51:57,56
Ashley Wilkes is still alive to come home to the women who love him

00:51:57,98 --> 00:51:59,40
both of them.

00:52:36,10 --> 00:52:37,56
Oh, you're here.

00:52:41,06 --> 00:52:43,98
Oh, you're here. You're really here at last.

00:52:44,27 --> 00:52:46,65
Oh, my dear, I've waited so long.

00:52:46,69 --> 00:52:49,07
Melanie, my dear, my darling wife.

00:52:53,07 --> 00:52:55,08
Oh, but we're forgetting Scarlett.

00:52:56,58 --> 00:52:57,87
Scarlett, dear.

