Oh, you mustn't say that. It's bad luck. Say a prayer quickly.

00:56:32,67 --> 00:56:34,17
You say one for me.

00:56:35,17 --> 00:56:38,59
We shall need all our prayers now the end is coming.

00:56:38,88 --> 00:56:39,93
The end?

00:56:39,97 --> 00:56:41,39
The end of the war.

00:56:42,18 --> 00:56:44,10
And the end of our world, Scarlett.

00:56:45,47 --> 00:56:48,43
But, Ashley, you don't think the Yankees are beating us?

00:56:48,48 --> 00:56:52,75
Oh, Scarlett, my men are barefooted now

00:56:52,78 --> 00:56:54,97
and the snow in Virginia is deep.

00:56:55,57 --> 00:56:56,98
When I see them

00:56:57,36 --> 00:57:01,78
and I see the Yankees coming and coming, always more and more.

00:57:04,78 --> 00:57:07,49
Well, when the end does come I shall be far away.

00:57:07,99 --> 00:57:11,00
It'll be a comfort to me to know that she has you.

00:57:12,08 --> 00:57:14,17
You will promise, won't you?

00:57:16,67 --> 00:57:17,67
Yes.

00:57:19,09 --> 00:57:20,76
Is that all, Ashley?

00:57:21,76 --> 00:57:24,39
All except, goodbye.

00:57:24,97 --> 00:57:26,93
Oh, Ashley, I can't let you go.

00:57:26,97 --> 00:57:28,22
You must be brave... No....

00:57:28,27 --> 00:57:29,48
You must.

00:57:30,06 --> 00:57:32,06
How else can I bear going?

00:57:32,90 --> 00:57:36,57
Oh, Scarlett, you are so fine and strong and beautiful.

00:57:37,86 --> 00:57:39,78
Not just your sweet face, my dear

00:57:40,78 --> 00:57:42,20
but you.

00:57:45,37 --> 00:57:47,58
Oh, Ashley, kiss me.

00:57:48,37 --> 00:57:50,08
Kiss me goodbye.

00:57:56,79 --> 00:57:57,75
No, Scarlett.

00:57:57,80 --> 00:57:59,38
Oh, Ashley, I love you.

00:57:59,96 --> 00:58:02,88
I've always loved you. I never loved anyone else.

00:58:03,18 --> 00:58:05,64
I only married Charles just to hurt you.

00:58:05,68 --> 00:58:08,10
Oh, Ashley. Tell me you love me.

00:58:09,10 --> 00:58:11,56
I'll live on it the rest of my life.

00:58:13,48 --> 00:58:14,56
Goodbye.

00:58:34,50 --> 00:58:36,67
When the war is over, Ashley.

00:58:37,46 --> 00:58:39,46
When the war is over.

00:58:59,69 --> 00:59:01,36
And there's a place back home

00:59:02,19 --> 00:59:05,36
where a wild plum tree comes to flower in the springtime.

00:59:06,70 --> 00:59:08,37
Down by the creek, you know.

00:59:08,87 --> 00:59:10,37
Yes, I know, I know.

00:59:11,29 --> 00:59:14,62
When we were little, my brother, Jeff, and I used to.

00:59:14,66 --> 00:59:18,17
I told you about my brother, Jeff, didn't l, ma'am?

00:59:18,67 --> 00:59:19,96
I know I did.

00:59:20,38 --> 00:59:21,63
He.

00:59:21,67 --> 00:59:24,59
We don't know where Jeff is now, ma'am.

00:59:25,09 --> 00:59:28,39
Since Bull Run we haven't heard anything and.

00:59:28,89 --> 00:59:31,22
Please, we must have your temperature now.

00:59:31,26 --> 00:59:33,93
Just take this in your mouth and not talk anymore.

00:59:33,97 --> 00:59:35,48
Not just now.

00:59:35,89 --> 00:59:38,69
Melanie, I'm so tired I've gotta go home.

00:59:39,77 --> 00:59:41,48
Aren't you tired, Melanie?

00:59:41,98 --> 00:59:44,57
No, I'm not tired, Scarlett.

00:59:45,28 --> 00:59:47,03
This might be

00:59:47,07 --> 00:59:48,07
Ashley.

00:59:48,86 --> 00:59:51,66
And only strangers here to comfort him.

00:59:52,08 --> 00:59:54,08
No, I'm not tired, Scarlett.

00:59:55,29 --> 00:59:57,00
They could all be

00:59:57,50 --> 00:59:58,79
Ashley.

01:00:10,97 --> 01:00:14,93
I've been sittin' by this curb one solid hour waitin' to speak to you, Miss Wilkes.

01:00:14,97 --> 01:00:17,73
Go on, you trash, don't you be pesterin' these ladies.

01:00:17,77 --> 01:00:19,35
Don't talk to her, Melly.

01:00:19,40 --> 01:00:21,73
It's all right, Scarlett. Who are you?

01:00:21,77 --> 01:00:24,53
My name's Belle Watlin'. But that don't matter.

01:00:24,57 --> 01:00:26,83
I expect you think I've got no business here.

01:00:26,86 --> 01:00:29,54
Hadn't you best tell me what you want to see me about?

01:00:29,57 --> 01:00:32,95
First time I come here, I says, Belle, you're a nurse.

01:00:32,99 --> 01:00:35,12
But the ladies didn't want my kind of nursin'.

01:00:35,16 --> 01:00:37,33
Well, they was more than likely right.

01:00:37,37 --> 01:00:39,25
Then I tried givin' 'em money.

01:00:39,29 --> 01:00:41,83
My money wasn't good enough for 'em, either.

01:00:41,88 --> 01:00:43,17
Old pea-hens.

01:00:43,67 --> 01:00:46,09
I know a gentleman who says you're a human bein'.

01:00:46,38 --> 01:00:50,05
If you are, which they ain't, you'll take my money for the hospital.

01:00:50,09 --> 01:00:53,35
What are you doing here? Haven't you been told twice already?

01:00:53,39 --> 01:00:55,43
This time I'm conversin' with Miss Wilkes.

01:00:55,47 --> 01:00:57,43
You might as well take my money, Miss Wilkes.

01:00:57,47 --> 01:01:00,22
It's good money, even if it is mine.

01:01:00,25 --> 01:01:01,36
I'm sure you're very generous.

01:01:01,40 --> 01:01:04,52
No, I'm not. I'm a Confederate like everybody else, that's all.

01:01:04,57 --> 01:01:06,16
Of course you are.

01:01:06,19 --> 01:01:08,44
There's some folks here wouldn't feel that way.

01:01:08,49 --> 01:01:11,07
But maybe they ain't as good Christians as you.

01:01:18,29 --> 01:01:21,08
Look, Mrs. Meade. It's a great deal of money.

01:01:21,37 --> 01:01:23,58
$Ten, $20, $30, $50.

01:01:23,96 --> 01:01:26,30
And it's not our paper money. It's gold.

01:01:26,88 --> 01:01:28,59
Let me see that handkerchief.

01:01:28,96 --> 01:01:30,59
R. B.

01:01:32,59 --> 01:01:35,76
And she's driving away in Rhett Butler's carriage.

01:01:36,68 --> 01:01:39,77
Oh, if I just wasn't a lady what wouldn't I tell that varmint.

01:02:14,68 --> 01:02:17,64
The Lord is my Shepherd. I shall not want.

01:02:17,68 --> 01:02:20,27
He maketh me to lie down in green pastures.

01:02:20,68 --> 01:02:21,77
He leadeth.

01:02:24,19 --> 01:02:26,45
He restoreth my soul.

01:02:26,48 --> 01:02:29,86
He leadeth me in the paths of righteousness for His name's sake.

01:02:30,57 --> 01:02:33,78
Yeah, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death

01:02:34,20 --> 01:02:35,78
I will fear no evil.

01:02:36,07 --> 01:02:37,37
For Thou art with me.

01:02:37,66 --> 01:02:40,16
Thy rod and Thy staff, they comfort me.

01:02:41,29 --> 01:02:42,29
Yankees.

01:02:42,87 --> 01:02:45,92
The Yankees. Dr. Meade, they're getting closer.

01:02:45,96 --> 01:02:50,59
They'll never get into Atlanta. They'll never get through old Peg-Leg Hood.

01:02:51,59 --> 01:02:53,76
Give me something for the pain.

01:02:54,17 --> 01:02:55,93
Give me something for the pain.

01:02:56,62 --> 01:02:59,75
Sorry, son, we haven't got anything to give you.

01:03:00,86 --> 01:03:03,29
These animaIs is driving me crazy.

01:03:03,96 --> 01:03:06,12
What luck. You've got my jack.

01:03:06,19 --> 01:03:08,79
Give me an ace and I'll start another war.

01:03:08,86 --> 01:03:10,52
I'll bid the moon.

01:03:14,43 --> 01:03:18,49
I'll never see you or Pa again.

01:03:19,47 --> 01:03:21,20
This leg's got to come off, soldier.

01:03:21,27 --> 01:03:23,60
No, no. Leave me alone.

01:03:23,71 --> 01:03:24,83
I'm sorry, soldier.

01:03:24,91 --> 01:03:27,25
We're all run out of chloroform, Dr. Meade.

01:03:27,28 --> 01:03:28,57
Then we'll have to operate without it.

01:03:28,65 --> 01:03:30,48
No, no. Leave me alone.

01:03:30,52 --> 01:03:32,82
You can't do it. I won't let you do it to me.

01:03:32,85 --> 01:03:36,08
Tell Dr. Wilson to take this leg off immediately. It's gangrene.

01:03:36,15 --> 01:03:38,25
No, no. Don't.

01:03:38,29 --> 01:03:41,12
I haven't seen my family in three days.

01:03:41,15 --> 01:03:43,42
I'm going home for haIf an hour.

01:03:43,53 --> 01:03:45,09
Orderly. Give me a lift.

01:03:49,23 --> 01:03:51,46
Nurse, you can free this bed.

01:03:52,47 --> 01:03:53,99
Miss Scarlett.

01:03:55,64 --> 01:03:57,34
Why, Frank Kennedy.

01:03:57,41 --> 01:03:59,47
Miss Suellen, is she well?

01:03:59,68 --> 01:04:03,59
When did they bring you in? You all right? Are you badly hurt?

01:04:03,62 --> 01:04:06,21
But Miss Suellen, is she... She's all right, but I

01:04:06,24 --> 01:04:08,39
Dr. Wilson needs you in the operating room.

01:04:08,43 --> 01:04:10,54
He's going to take off that leg. Better hurry.

01:04:11,82 --> 01:04:13,26
I'll be back.

01:04:14,86 --> 01:04:19,30
No, no, leave me alone.

01:04:19,33 --> 01:04:23,74
No, no, I can't stand it.

01:04:24,40 --> 01:04:25,73
Don't cut.

01:04:26,30 --> 01:04:28,10
Don't, don't.

01:04:28,47 --> 01:04:29,60
Please.

01:04:30,01 --> 01:04:31,70
Where's the nurse?

01:04:35,94 --> 01:04:37,35
Dr. Wilson's waiting.

01:04:37,98 --> 01:04:39,62
Let him wait. I'm going home. I've done enough.

01:04:39,65 --> 01:04:43,48
I don't want any more men dying. I don't want any more.

01:05:44,28 --> 01:05:46,10
Big Sam.

01:05:46,52 --> 01:05:48,49
Big Sam. Big Sam.

01:05:49,59 --> 01:05:53,51
Almighty Moses, it's Miss Scarlett.

01:05:53,86 --> 01:05:54,98
Big Sam.

01:05:55,06 --> 01:05:59,14
Sam, I'm so glad to see you.

01:05:59,38 --> 01:06:02,27
Tell me about Tara, about my mother. She didn't write me.

01:06:02,31 --> 01:06:04,13
She's gone and got sick, Miss Scarlett. Sick?

01:06:04,16 --> 01:06:04,93
Just a little bit sick, that's all.

01:06:04,97 --> 01:06:09,30
Your pa was wild when they wouldn't let him fight 'cause of his broken knee.

01:06:09,34 --> 01:06:13,64
He had fits when they took us field hands to dig ditches for white soldiers to hide in.

01:06:13,67 --> 01:06:14,68
But your ma says the Confederacy needs us.

01:06:14,75 --> 01:06:16,18
So we's gonna dig for the South.

01:06:16,25 --> 01:06:17,37
Sam, was there a doctor?

01:06:17,45 --> 01:06:18,57
Ma'am, we've got to march.

01:06:18,65 --> 01:06:21,48
Goodbye, Miss Scarlett. Don't worry, we'll stop them Yankees.

01:06:21,55 --> 01:06:26,25
Goodbye, Big Sam. Goodbye, boys. If any of you get sick or hurt, let me know.

01:06:26,28 --> 01:06:27,07
Goodbye, Miss Scarlett. Goodbye.

01:06:27,10 --> 01:06:28,49
Goodbye. Goodbye.

01:06:48,65 --> 01:06:49,81
Scarlett.

01:06:49,98 --> 01:06:51,18
Scarlett.

01:06:54,49 --> 01:06:58,58
Climb into this buggy. This is no day for walking.

01:06:58,61 --> 01:06:58,85
You'll get run over.

01:06:58,92 --> 01:07:00,15
Oh, Rhett.

01:07:00,63 --> 01:07:02,86
Drive me to Aunt Pitty's, please.

01:07:04,43 --> 01:07:06,83
Panic's a pretty sight, isn't it?

01:07:09,67 --> 01:07:12,26
That's just another of Gen. Sherman's calling cards.

01:07:12,34 --> 01:07:13,70
He'll be paying us a visit soon.

01:07:13,74 --> 01:07:17,46
I've got to get out of here before the Yankees come.

01:07:17,49 --> 01:07:18,54
And leave your work at the hospital?

01:07:18,58 --> 01:07:22,38
Or have you had enough of death and lice and men chopped up?

01:07:22,45 --> 01:07:24,75
I suppose you weren't meant for sick men, Scarlett.

01:07:24,82 --> 01:07:28,10
Don't talk to me like that. I'm so scared.

01:07:28,13 --> 01:07:29,31
I wish I could get out of here.

01:07:29,34 --> 01:07:30,49
Let's get out of here together.

01:07:30,56 --> 01:07:33,79
No use staying here and letting the South come down around your ears.

01:07:33,86 --> 01:07:36,66
There are too many nice places to go and visit.

01:07:36,73 --> 01:07:39,03
Mexico, London, Paris

01:07:39,10 --> 01:07:40,96
With you? Yes, ma'am.

01:07:41,27 --> 01:07:44,70
With a man who understands you and admires you for just what you are.

01:07:44,77 --> 01:07:47,86
I figure we belong together, being the same sort.

01:07:48,24 --> 01:07:52,90
I've been waiting for you to grow up and get that sad-eyed Ashley out of your heart.

01:07:52,98 --> 01:07:57,41
Well, I hear Mrs. Wilkes is going to have a baby in another month or so.

01:07:57,48 --> 01:08:01,44
It'll be hard loving a man with a wife and baby clinging to him.

01:08:03,86 --> 01:08:08,21
Well, here we are. Are you going with me, or are you getting out?

01:08:08,23 --> 01:08:13,03
I hate and despise you, Rhett Butler, and I'll hate and despise you till I die.

01:08:13,73 --> 01:08:16,60
Oh, no, you won't, Scarlett. Not that long.

01:08:24,14 --> 01:08:25,71
Miss Scarlett. Miss Scarlett.

01:08:25,74 --> 01:08:30,22
Folks is all going to Macon and folks is running away and running away.

01:08:30,25 --> 01:08:32,89
I can't bear it. Those cannon balls right in my ears.

01:08:32,95 --> 01:08:35,18
I faint every time I hear one.

01:08:36,12 --> 01:08:38,45
Uncle Peter, look out for that trunk.

01:08:38,52 --> 01:08:40,15
But, Aunt Pitty, you aren't leaving?

01:08:40,22 --> 01:08:43,13
I may be a coward, but oh, dear.

01:08:43,16 --> 01:08:44,99
Yankees in Georgia.

01:08:45,20 --> 01:08:46,29
How did they ever get in?

01:08:46,36 --> 01:08:50,16
I'm going, too. Prissy, go pack my things. Get them, quick.

01:08:50,19 --> 01:08:50,97
Wait, Aunt Pitty, I won't be a minute.

01:08:51,00 --> 01:08:53,52
Scarlett, do you really think you ought to?

01:08:53,55 --> 01:08:54,14
Scarlett.

01:08:54,17 --> 01:08:57,17
What is this? You ain't planning on running away?

01:08:57,21 --> 01:09:01,41
And don't you dare try to stop me. I'm never going back to that hospital.

01:09:01,44 --> 01:09:03,77
I've had enough of smelling death and rot and death.

01:09:03,85 --> 01:09:06,94
I'm going home. I want my mother. My mother needs me.

01:09:07,02 --> 01:09:09,75
Now you've got to listen to me. You must stay here.

01:09:09,79 --> 01:09:13,17
Without a chaperon, Dr. Meade? It simply isn't done.

01:09:13,20 --> 01:09:16,55
Good heavens, woman, this is war, not a garden party.

01:09:16,58 --> 01:09:18,29
You've got to stay. Melanie needs you.

01:09:18,33 --> 01:09:22,59
She's ill already. She shouldn't even be having a baby.

01:09:22,62 --> 01:09:23,43
Can't we take her along?

01:09:23,50 --> 01:09:24,99
Do you want her to take that chance?

01:09:25,07 --> 01:09:26,63
To be jounced over rough roads

01:09:26,70 --> 01:09:28,64
and have her baby ahead of time, in a buggy?

01:09:28,71 --> 01:09:30,57
It isn't my baby. You take care of her.

01:09:30,64 --> 01:09:32,51
Scarlett. We haven't enough doctors

01:09:32,58 --> 01:09:35,84
much less nurses to look after a sick woman.

01:09:35,87 --> 01:09:37,56
You've got to stay for Melanie.

01:09:37,65 --> 01:09:40,02
I don't know anything about babies being born.

01:09:40,05 --> 01:09:41,28
I knows, I knows.

01:09:41,35 --> 01:09:45,48
I knows how to do it. I's done it lots and lots.

01:09:45,51 --> 01:09:47,26
Let me, Doctor, let me. I can do everything.

01:09:47,29 --> 01:09:50,39
Good. Then I'll rely on you to help us. Yes, Doctor.

01:09:50,46 --> 01:09:53,69
Ashley's fighting in the field, fighting for the cause.

01:09:53,76 --> 01:09:56,65
He may never come back. He may die.

01:09:56,68 --> 01:09:59,53
Scarlett, we owe him a well-born child.

01:10:00,04 --> 01:10:01,10
Ashley.

01:10:01,17 --> 01:10:05,17
If you're coming, Scarlett, hurry.

01:10:05,20 --> 01:10:05,67
I promised Ashley

01:10:05,74 --> 01:10:06,88
something.

01:10:06,91 --> 01:10:08,44
Then you'll stay?

01:10:08,88 --> 01:10:12,01
Good. Go along, Miss Pittypat. Scarlett's staying.

01:10:12,08 --> 01:10:16,87
Go on, Uncle Peter. Oh, dear, I don't know what to do.

01:10:16,90 --> 01:10:19,50
It's like the end of the world.

01:10:19,53 --> 01:10:22,09
Uncle Peter, my smelling salts.

01:10:28,87 --> 01:10:31,16
Melanie, it's all your fault.

01:10:31,74 --> 01:10:33,99
I hate you, I hate you.

01:10:34,02 --> 01:10:35,60
And I hate your baby.

01:10:35,71 --> 01:10:38,04
If only I hadn't promised Ashley.

01:10:38,11 --> 01:10:40,34
If only I hadn't promised him.

01:11:09,41 --> 01:11:11,81
Stop. Stop, please stop.

01:11:11,84 --> 01:11:13,48
Is it true? Are the Yankees coming?

01:11:13,51 --> 01:11:15,54
I'm afraid so, ma'am. The Army's pulling out.

01:11:15,58 --> 01:11:18,78
Pulling out of Atlanta? Leaving us to the Yankees?

01:11:18,81 --> 01:11:19,38
Not leaving, ma'am, evacuating.

01:11:19,42 --> 01:11:23,27
We've got to before Sherman cuts the McDonough Road and catches us.

01:11:23,30 --> 01:11:25,55
It can't be true. It can't be true. What'll I do?

01:11:25,59 --> 01:11:29,75
Better refugee south right quick, ma'am. If you'll excuse me, ma'am.

01:11:30,49 --> 01:11:32,60
Prissy.

01:11:32,63 --> 01:11:34,26
Prissy, come here.

01:11:34,33 --> 01:11:37,79
Pack my things and Miss Melanie's, too. We're going to Tara right away.

01:11:37,87 --> 01:11:38,93
The Yankees are coming.

01:11:39,00 --> 01:11:41,05
Yes, ma'am.

01:11:41,81 --> 01:11:42,83
Scarlett.

01:11:42,90 --> 01:11:44,47
Scarlett.

01:11:44,88 --> 01:11:47,43
Melly, we're going to

01:11:49,21 --> 01:11:50,31
Melly.

01:11:52,95 --> 01:11:56,28
I'm sorry to be such a bother, Scarlett.

01:11:58,82 --> 01:12:02,97
It began at daybreak.

01:12:03,00 --> 01:12:03,83
But, but

01:12:03,86 --> 01:12:06,11
But the Yankees are coming.

01:12:07,13 --> 01:12:08,66
Poor Scarlett.

01:12:09,17 --> 01:12:12,29
You'd be at Tara now with your mother, wouldn't you

01:12:13,10 --> 01:12:14,94
if it weren't for me?

01:12:15,57 --> 01:12:17,40
Oh, Scarlett, darling

01:12:17,81 --> 01:12:19,71
you've been so good to me.

01:12:19,81 --> 01:12:23,18
No sister could have been sweeter.

01:12:25,52 --> 01:12:27,85
I've been lying here thinking

01:12:28,62 --> 01:12:30,31
if I should die

01:12:31,36 --> 01:12:33,38
will you take my baby?

01:12:35,69 --> 01:12:37,72
Oh, fiddle-dee-dee, Melly.

01:12:37,80 --> 01:12:41,13
Aren't things bad enough without you talking about dying?

01:12:41,17 --> 01:12:44,07
I'll send for Dr. Meade right away. Not yet, Scarlett.

01:12:44,14 --> 01:12:47,97
I couldn't let Dr. Meade sit here for hours, while

01:12:48,00 --> 01:12:51,80
while all those poor, wounded boys... Prissy.

01:12:52,84 --> 01:12:56,65
Prissy. Prissy. Come here, quick.

01:12:56,71 --> 01:12:59,75
Yes, ma'am. The baby.

01:12:59,78 --> 01:13:02,91
Well, don't stand there like a scared goat. Run.

01:13:04,66 --> 01:13:09,63
Hurry. I'll sell you South, I will. I swear I will.

01:13:10,39 --> 01:13:12,93
Where's that Prissy?

01:13:15,20 --> 01:13:17,29
This room's like an oven already

01:13:17,37 --> 01:13:19,30
and it isn't noon yet.

01:13:22,14 --> 01:13:23,94
Oh, don't worry, Melly.

01:13:24,48 --> 01:13:28,14
Mother says it always seems like the doctor will never come.

01:13:29,35 --> 01:13:32,04
If I don't take a strap to that Prissy.

01:13:39,39 --> 01:13:40,62
Oh, Melly.

01:13:41,29 --> 01:13:43,89
You know what I heard about Maybelle Merriwether?

01:13:43,96 --> 01:13:46,16
You remember that funny-looking beau of hers?

01:13:46,23 --> 01:13:50,41
The one with a uniform like ladies' red flannel underdrawers.

01:13:50,44 --> 01:13:53,24
You don't have to keep on talking for my sake, Scarlett.

01:13:53,40 --> 01:13:55,37
I know how worried you are.

01:14:08,62 --> 01:14:12,28
Oh, Melly, I'll just go and fetch you some cool water.

01:14:13,86 --> 01:14:16,34
You're as slow as molasses in January.

01:14:16,37 --> 01:14:17,13
And where's Dr. Meade?

01:14:17,16 --> 01:14:19,49
I ain't never seen him, Miss Scarlett. What?

01:14:19,56 --> 01:14:21,96
No, ma'am. He ain't at the hospital.

01:14:22,00 --> 01:14:28,02
A man, he told me the doctor's down at the car shed with the wounded soldiers

01:14:28,05 --> 01:14:29,59
Well, why didn't you go after him?

01:14:29,77 --> 01:14:30,97
Miss Scarlett.

01:14:31,04 --> 01:14:34,19
I's scared to go down there to the car shed.

01:14:34,38 --> 01:14:38,31
There's folks dying down there and I's scared of dead folks.

01:14:40,45 --> 01:14:42,15
Oh, you go sit by Miss Melly.

01:14:42,22 --> 01:14:46,05
And don't you be upsetting her, or I'll whip the hide off you.

01:15:23,93 --> 01:15:26,52
Have you seen Dr. Meade? Side, lady, please.

01:15:30,47 --> 01:15:31,80
Dr. Meade.

01:16:16,45 --> 01:16:18,18
Dr. Meade. At last.

01:16:18,32 --> 01:16:21,61
Oh, thank heavens you're here. I need every pair of hands.

01:16:21,69 --> 01:16:24,59
Come, child. Wake up. We've got work to do.

01:16:24,96 --> 01:16:28,48
But Melly's having her baby. You've got to come with me.

01:16:28,59 --> 01:16:31,46
Are you crazy? I can't leave these men for a baby.

01:16:31,53 --> 01:16:34,97
They're dying, hundreds of them. Get some woman to help you.

01:16:35,00 --> 01:16:38,41
But there isn't anybody. Dr. Meade, she might die.

01:16:38,44 --> 01:16:38,66
Die.

01:16:38,74 --> 01:16:41,70
Look at them. Bleeding to death in front of my eyes.

01:16:41,74 --> 01:16:46,24
No chloroform. No bandages. Nothing. Nothing to even ease their pain.

01:16:46,38 --> 01:16:48,74
Now run along and don't bother me.

01:16:48,81 --> 01:16:52,11
Now don't worry, child. There's nothing to bringing a baby.

01:16:52,18 --> 01:16:54,22
Now bring those stretchers in here.

01:16:54,25 --> 01:16:55,36
Dr. Meade.

01:16:55,39 --> 01:16:56,47
I'm coming.

01:17:15,57 --> 01:17:17,13
Is the doctor come?

01:17:17,78 --> 01:17:19,21
No, he can't come.

01:17:19,28 --> 01:17:22,07
Oh, Miss Scarlett, Miss Melly bad off.

01:17:22,21 --> 01:17:24,81
He can't come. There's nobody to come.

01:17:25,52 --> 01:17:29,04
Prissy, you've got to manage without the doctor. I'll help you.

01:17:29,12 --> 01:17:32,47
Oh, lordy, Miss Scarlett.

01:17:32,50 --> 01:17:33,42
Well, what is it?

01:17:33,49 --> 01:17:35,75
Lordy, we've got to have a doctor.

01:17:35,83 --> 01:17:38,66
I don't know nothing about birthing babies.

01:17:40,00 --> 01:17:41,83
What do you mean? I don't know

01:17:41,90 --> 01:17:44,25
You told me you knew everything about it.

01:17:44,28 --> 01:17:45,90
I don't know how come I told such a lie.

01:17:45,94 --> 01:17:49,46
Ma ain't never let me around when folks was having them.

01:17:49,87 --> 01:17:50,97
Scarlett.

01:17:51,58 --> 01:17:52,70
Scarlett.

01:17:53,41 --> 01:17:55,28
Oh, Miss Scarlett

01:17:55,88 --> 01:17:57,11
Stop it.

01:17:58,62 --> 01:18:00,05
Go light a fire in the stove.

01:18:00,12 --> 01:18:03,63
Keep boiling water in the kettle, get me the ball of twine and

01:18:03,66 --> 01:18:06,42
and all the clean toweIs you can find, and the scissors.

01:18:06,45 --> 01:18:07,75
Don't come telling me you can't find them.

01:18:07,78 --> 01:18:09,82
Go get them, and get them quick.

01:18:11,03 --> 01:18:12,29
Scarlett.

01:18:19,93 --> 01:18:20,86
Scarlett.

01:18:21,54 --> 01:18:22,87
Coming, Melly.

01:18:23,97 --> 01:18:25,17
Coming.

01:18:29,01 --> 01:18:31,31
Go, Scarlett, before the Yankees get here.

01:18:31,38 --> 01:18:33,37
I'm not afraid. You know I won't leave you.

01:18:33,45 --> 01:18:35,15
It's no use. I'm going to die.

01:18:35,22 --> 01:18:39,04
Don't be a goose, Melly. Hold on to me. Hold on to me.

01:18:39,07 --> 01:18:40,98
Talk to me, Scarlett.

01:18:41,01 --> 01:18:42,89
Please talk to me.

01:18:43,06 --> 01:18:44,39
Don't try to be brave, Melly.

01:18:44,43 --> 01:18:46,83
Yell all you want, there's nobody to hear.

01:18:46,90 --> 01:18:51,23
Ma says that if you puts a knife under the bed, it cuts the pain in two.

01:18:56,64 --> 01:18:58,40
Capt. Butler.

01:18:59,28 --> 01:19:00,57
Capt. Butler.

01:19:02,35 --> 01:19:03,37
Who do you want?

01:19:03,45 --> 01:19:04,44
Capt. Butler.

01:19:04,52 --> 01:19:07,18
He's upstairs. Belle Watling's giving a party.

01:19:09,42 --> 01:19:10,61
Thank you.

01:19:12,96 --> 01:19:15,39
Capt. Butler. Oh, Capt. Butler.

01:19:15,63 --> 01:19:17,69
What's all the rumpus about?

01:19:17,86 --> 01:19:21,06
I's got a message for Capt. Butler, Miss Watling.

01:19:21,27 --> 01:19:24,72
Capt. Butler, you come out here in the streets to me.

01:19:25,94 --> 01:19:27,07
What is it, Prissy?

01:19:27,10 --> 01:19:30,23
Miss Scarlett, she done sent me for you.

01:19:30,26 --> 01:19:33,36
Miss Melly, she done had her baby today.

01:19:33,39 --> 01:19:36,35
A fine baby boy

01:19:36,38 --> 01:19:39,14
and Miss Scarlett and me, we brung him.

01:19:39,22 --> 01:19:40,92
Do you mean to tell me that Scarlett

01:19:40,95 --> 01:19:44,55
Well, it was mostly me, Capt. Butler, only Miss Scarlett

01:19:44,62 --> 01:19:50,46
she helped me a little, but I don't expect no doctor could have done no better.

01:19:50,49 --> 01:19:55,17
Only Miss Melly, she feeling kind of poorly now it's all over.

01:19:55,20 --> 01:19:56,40
Yes, I can believe that.

01:19:56,47 --> 01:20:00,23
And the Yankees is coming, and Miss Scarlett, she said

01:20:01,34 --> 01:20:04,71
Oh, Capt. Butler, the Yankees is here.

01:20:04,74 --> 01:20:08,11
Please come and bring your carriage for us right away.

01:20:08,15 --> 01:20:11,23
I'm sorry, Prissy, but the Army took my horse and carriage.

01:20:11,26 --> 01:20:13,64
You'd better come upstairs. I'll see what I can do.

01:20:13,67 --> 01:20:14,98
Oh, no, Capt. Butler.

01:20:15,25 --> 01:20:20,68
Ma would wear me out with a cornstalk if I was to go into Miss Watling's.

01:20:21,16 --> 01:20:24,79
Any of you beauties know where I can steal a horse for a good cause?

01:20:31,70 --> 01:20:34,54
Whoa, Marse Robert. Is that you, Rhett?

01:20:34,81 --> 01:20:38,81
We's here, Miss Scarlett. We's here. Rhett, I knew you'd come.

01:20:38,84 --> 01:20:39,78
Good evening. Nice weather we're having.

01:20:39,81 --> 01:20:41,94
Prissy tells me you're planning on taking a trip.

01:20:41,98 --> 01:20:44,07
If you make any jokes now, I'll kill you.

01:20:44,15 --> 01:20:45,48
Don't tell me you're frightened.

01:20:45,55 --> 01:20:49,51
I'm scared to death. If you had the sense of a goat, you'd be scared too.

01:20:49,59 --> 01:20:51,58
Oh, the Yankees. No, not yet.

01:20:51,66 --> 01:20:54,39
That's what's left of our Army, blowing up the ammunition

01:20:54,46 --> 01:20:55,58
so the Yankees won't get it.

01:20:55,66 --> 01:20:57,35
We've got to get out of here.

01:20:57,43 --> 01:20:58,42
At your service, madam.

01:20:58,50 --> 01:21:00,72
Just where are you figuring on going?

01:21:00,75 --> 01:21:01,23
Home, to Tara.

01:21:01,27 --> 01:21:03,63
They've been fighting all day around Tara.

01:21:03,67 --> 01:21:06,00
Do you think you can parade through the Yankee Army

01:21:06,07 --> 01:21:08,83
with a sick woman, a baby, and a simple-minded darky

01:21:08,86 --> 01:21:10,27
or do you intend leaving them behind?

01:21:10,34 --> 01:21:12,87
They're going with me. I'm going home. You can't stop me.

01:21:12,94 --> 01:21:16,67
Don't you know it's dangerous jouncing Mrs. Wilkes over miles of open country?

01:21:16,75 --> 01:21:18,18
I want my mother.

01:21:19,05 --> 01:21:20,95
I want to go home to Tara.

01:21:21,02 --> 01:21:22,85
Tara's probably been burned to the ground.

01:21:22,89 --> 01:21:25,20
The woods are full of stragglers from both armies.

01:21:25,24 --> 01:21:27,52
The least they'll do is take the horse away from you.

01:21:27,59 --> 01:21:30,19
It isn't much of an animal, but I had trouble stealing it.

01:21:30,26 --> 01:21:33,32
I'm going home if I have to walk every step of the way.

01:21:33,40 --> 01:21:36,59
I'll kill you if you try to stop me. I will, I will.

01:21:37,10 --> 01:21:41,59
I will.

01:21:44,01 --> 01:21:47,53
All right, darling, all right. Now you shall go home.

01:21:49,41 --> 01:21:53,70
I guess anybody who did what you've done today can take care of Sherman.

01:21:54,48 --> 01:21:56,82
Here, now. Stop crying.

01:21:59,32 --> 01:22:01,62
Now blow your nose like a good little girl.

01:22:01,89 --> 01:22:03,05
There.

01:22:14,77 --> 01:22:15,86
Prissy. What are you doing?

01:22:15,94 --> 01:22:17,37
I's packing, Miss Scarlett.

01:22:17,44 --> 01:22:20,31
Stop it and come get the baby.

01:22:22,75 --> 01:22:23,87
Melly.

01:22:24,88 --> 01:22:27,71
Mrs. Wilkes, we're taking you to Tara.

01:22:27,95 --> 01:22:29,05
Tara

01:22:29,09 --> 01:22:30,99
It's the only way, Melly. No.

01:22:31,02 --> 01:22:34,26
Sherman will burn the house over our heads if we stay.

01:22:34,29 --> 01:22:35,46
It's all right, Melly.

01:22:35,53 --> 01:22:37,08
My baby.

01:22:37,69 --> 01:22:39,22
My poor baby.

01:22:43,77 --> 01:22:46,20
Have you the strength to put your arms around my neck?

01:22:46,27 --> 01:22:48,03
I think so.

01:22:50,84 --> 01:22:52,10
Never mind.

01:22:52,18 --> 01:22:54,58
Oh, Ashley, Charles

01:22:54,61 --> 01:22:56,24
What is it? What does she want?

01:22:56,28 --> 01:22:59,11
Ashley's picture, Charles' sword. She wants us to bring them.

01:22:59,18 --> 01:23:00,21
Get them.

01:23:16,17 --> 01:23:17,22
What's that?

01:23:17,47 --> 01:23:20,59
Our gallant lads must have set fire to the warehouses near the depot.

01:23:20,62 --> 01:23:23,70
There's enough ammunition in the boxcars to blow us to Tara.

01:23:23,74 --> 01:23:25,74
We'll have to hurry to get across the tracks.

01:23:25,78 --> 01:23:27,58
You're not going that way. We have to.

01:23:27,61 --> 01:23:30,77
The McDonough Road's the only one the Yankees haven't cut yet.

01:23:40,02 --> 01:23:42,46
Oh, wait. I forgot to lock the front door.

01:23:42,59 --> 01:23:43,93
What are you laughing at?

01:23:43,96 --> 01:23:46,11
At you, locking the Yankees out.

01:24:03,15 --> 01:24:04,77
Oh, dear, I wish they'd hurry.

01:24:04,85 --> 01:24:07,58
I wouldn't be in such a hurry to see them go if I were you.

01:24:07,65 --> 01:24:11,68
With them goes the last semblance of law and order.

01:24:12,49 --> 01:24:14,65
The scavengers aren't wasting any time.

01:24:19,13 --> 01:24:21,31
We've got to get out of here fast.

01:24:21,34 --> 01:24:22,16
There's a horse.

01:24:26,02 --> 01:24:27,92
Stay the horse

01:24:33,64 --> 01:24:35,30
Down the alley, cut them off.

01:24:49,29 --> 01:24:50,99
Give me that horse.

01:25:01,17 --> 01:25:02,20
Miss Scarlett.

01:25:06,54 --> 01:25:09,17
They haven't left much for the Yankees to take, have they?

01:25:09,25 --> 01:25:12,70
We'll have to make a dash for it before the fire reaches that ammunition.

01:25:33,87 --> 01:25:35,89
Come on.

01:25:39,44 --> 01:25:41,10
Throw me your shawl.

01:25:43,78 --> 01:25:47,34
Sorry, but you'll like it better if you don't see anything.

01:26:46,71 --> 01:26:48,78
Take a good look, my dear.

01:26:49,15 --> 01:26:50,17
It's a historic moment.

01:26:50,25 --> 01:26:51,71
You can tell your grandchildren

01:26:51,78 --> 01:26:55,01
how you watched the old South disappear one night.

01:27:11,37 --> 01:27:13,77
They were going to lick the Yankees in a month.

01:27:13,84 --> 01:27:15,70
Poor gallant fools.

01:27:15,74 --> 01:27:17,10
They make me sick, all of them.

01:27:17,17 --> 01:27:20,30
Getting us all into this with their swaggering and boasting.

01:27:20,64 --> 01:27:23,98
That's the way I feIt once about their swaggering and boasting.

01:27:24,85 --> 01:27:27,21
Rhett, I'm so glad you aren't with the Army.

01:27:27,28 --> 01:27:31,55
You can be proud now, proud that you've been smarter than all of them.

01:27:33,96 --> 01:27:35,74
I'm not so proud.

01:27:54,88 --> 01:27:55,94
Why did you stop?

01:27:56,01 --> 01:27:58,74
This is the turn to Tara. Let the horse breathe a bit.

01:27:59,12 --> 01:28:00,14
Mrs. Wilkes.

01:28:00,22 --> 01:28:03,52
Miss Melly done fainted way back, Capt. Butler.

01:28:03,72 --> 01:28:05,28
Well, she's probably better off.

01:28:05,36 --> 01:28:08,42
She couldn't stand the pain if she were conscious.

01:28:08,93 --> 01:28:11,79
Scarlett, are you still determined to do this crazy thing?

01:28:11,86 --> 01:28:14,69
Yes. I know we can get through, Rhett. I'm sure we can.

01:28:14,73 --> 01:28:16,60
Not we, my dear. You.

01:28:16,97 --> 01:28:18,43
I'm leaving you here.

01:28:18,74 --> 01:28:21,33
You're what? Rhett, where are you going?

01:28:21,57 --> 01:28:23,80
I'm going, my dear, to join the Army.

01:28:24,01 --> 01:28:27,34
You're joking. I could kill you for scaring me so.

01:28:27,37 --> 01:28:28,48
I'm very serious, Scarlett.

01:28:28,51 --> 01:28:31,24
I'm going to join up with our brave lads in gray.

01:28:31,31 --> 01:28:32,44
But they're running away.

01:28:32,52 --> 01:28:35,81
No. They'll turn and make a last stand, if I know anything about them.

01:28:35,89 --> 01:28:39,01
When they do, I'll be with them. A little late, but Better late

01:28:39,09 --> 01:28:40,82
Rhett, you must be joking.

01:28:41,86 --> 01:28:43,38
Selfish to the end, aren't you?

01:28:43,46 --> 01:28:47,90
Thinking only of your own precious hide, with never a thought for the noble cause.

01:28:47,93 --> 01:28:49,19
Rhett, how could you do this to me

01:28:49,27 --> 01:28:52,20
and why should you go now, after it's all over and I need you?

01:28:52,27 --> 01:28:53,26
Why? Why?

01:28:53,34 --> 01:28:54,36
Why?

01:28:54,44 --> 01:28:57,43
Maybe it's because I've always had a weakness for lost causes

01:28:57,51 --> 01:28:58,80
once they're really lost.

01:28:58,88 --> 01:28:59,97
Or maybe

01:29:01,21 --> 01:29:03,24
maybe I'm ashamed of myself.

01:29:04,48 --> 01:29:05,47
Who knows?

01:29:05,55 --> 01:29:08,95
You should die of shame to leave me here alone and helpless.

01:29:08,98 --> 01:29:10,19
You helpless?

01:29:11,25 --> 01:29:14,02
Heaven help the Yankees if they capture you.

01:29:14,56 --> 01:29:18,40
Now climb down here. I want to say goodbye.

01:29:18,43 --> 01:29:18,95
No.

01:29:19,56 --> 01:29:21,53
Climb down.

01:29:24,30 --> 01:29:27,63
Oh, Rhett, please don't go. You can't leave me, please.

01:29:27,70 --> 01:29:29,43
I'll never forgive you.

01:29:29,51 --> 01:29:34,13
I'm not asking you to forgive me. I'll never understand or forgive myself.

01:29:34,16 --> 01:29:38,05
And if a bullet gets me, so help me, I'll laugh at myseIf for being an idiot.

01:29:38,28 --> 01:29:39,91
But there's one thing I do know

01:29:39,98 --> 01:29:41,65
and that is that I love you, Scarlett.

01:29:41,68 --> 01:29:45,18
In spite of you, me and the whole silly world going to pieces around us

01:29:45,26 --> 01:29:46,35
I love you

01:29:46,42 --> 01:29:48,95
because we're alike. Bad lots, both of us.

01:29:49,33 --> 01:29:51,12
Selfish and shrewd

01:29:51,46 --> 01:29:54,83
but able to look things in the eyes and call them by their right names.

01:29:54,90 --> 01:29:56,80
Don't hold me like that.

01:29:56,90 --> 01:29:58,73
Scarlett, look at me.

01:29:59,90 --> 01:30:02,34
I love you more than I've ever loved any woman.

01:30:02,47 --> 01:30:05,70
And I've waited longer for you than I've ever waited for any woman.

01:30:05,78 --> 01:30:06,97
Let me alone.

01:30:08,14 --> 01:30:10,67
Here's a soldier of the South who loves you, Scarlett

01:30:10,75 --> 01:30:12,37
wants to feel your arms around him

01:30:12,45 --> 01:30:15,65
wants to carry the memory of your kisses into battle with him.

01:30:15,68 --> 01:30:17,01
Never mind about loving me.

01:30:17,09 --> 01:30:20,87
You're a woman sending a soldier to his death with a beautiful memory.

01:30:21,12 --> 01:30:22,92
Scarlett, kiss me.

01:30:24,06 --> 01:30:25,43
Kiss me, once.

01:30:30,77 --> 01:30:33,50
You low-down, cowardly, nasty thing, you.

01:30:33,54 --> 01:30:37,80
They were right. Everybody was right. You aren't a gentleman.

01:30:40,11 --> 01:30:42,27
A minor point at such a moment.

01:30:44,08 --> 01:30:45,78
Here.

01:30:45,82 --> 01:30:48,11
If anyone lays a hand on that nag, shoot him.

01:30:48,18 --> 01:30:50,15
But don't make a mistake and shoot the nag.

01:30:50,19 --> 01:30:54,32
Oh, go on. I want you to go. I hope a cannonball lands slap on you.

01:30:54,39 --> 01:30:56,22
I hope you're blown into a million pieces.

01:30:56,26 --> 01:30:58,79
Never mind the rest. I follow your general idea.

01:30:58,83 --> 01:31:01,32
And when I'm dead on the altar of my country

01:31:01,40 --> 01:31:03,73
I hope your conscience hurts you.

01:31:04,30 --> 01:31:05,73
Goodbye, Scarlett.

01:31:31,76 --> 01:31:34,36
Come on, you. We're going home.

01:32:50,11 --> 01:32:52,96
Oh, my poor baby.

01:32:54,01 --> 01:32:55,44
Don't worry, Melly.

01:32:55,68 --> 01:32:57,81
Mother will take care of him when we get home.

01:32:57,88 --> 01:33:01,36
Miss Scarlett, I's powerful hungry.

01:33:01,39 --> 01:33:03,53
We's got to have something to eat.

01:33:03,56 --> 01:33:04,42
Oh, hush up.

01:33:04,45 --> 01:33:07,45
We're nearly at Twelve Oaks. We'll stop there.

01:33:08,22 --> 01:33:10,21
Go on.

01:34:14,35 --> 01:34:19,70
Ashley, I'm glad you're not here to see this.

01:34:20,80 --> 01:34:22,49
The Yankees.

01:34:22,57 --> 01:34:24,50
The dirty Yankees.

01:34:39,15 --> 01:34:41,64
Prissy, come tie up this cow.

01:34:42,15 --> 01:34:44,55
We don't need no cow, Miss Scarlett.

01:34:44,59 --> 01:34:48,22
We'll be home soon, and I's scared of cows.

01:34:48,26 --> 01:34:51,39
Tear up your petticoat and tie her on to the back of the wagon.

01:34:51,53 --> 01:34:55,16
We need milk for the baby, and we don't know what we'll find at home.

01:35:04,41 --> 01:35:07,45
Melly. Melly, we're home.

01:35:07,48 --> 01:35:07,63
We're at Tara.

01:35:07,71 --> 01:35:11,12
Hurry. Move, you brute.

01:35:11,18 --> 01:35:13,61
Miss Scarlett, he's dead.

01:35:14,08 --> 01:35:18,35
