02:01:03,32 --> 02:01:06,26
Miss Scarlett, if true love carries any weight with you

02:01:06,33 --> 02:01:08,95
you can be sure your sister will be rich in that.

02:01:09,03 --> 02:01:12,66
I'll go out somewhere and get myseIf a little business if we're engaged.

02:01:12,73 --> 02:01:14,29
As soon as I get on my feet again

02:01:14,37 --> 02:01:16,86
All right, Frank. I'm sure I can speak for Pa.

02:01:16,87 --> 02:01:18,47
You go ask her now.

02:01:18,51 --> 02:01:21,68
Oh, thank you, Miss Scarlett.

02:01:24,71 --> 02:01:26,74
Excuse me, excuse me.

02:01:29,48 --> 02:01:32,45
Scarlett, what seems to be the trouble with Mr. Kennedy?

02:01:32,52 --> 02:01:34,48
More trouble than he guesses.

02:01:34,52 --> 02:01:36,42
He's finally asked for Suellen's hand.

02:01:36,49 --> 02:01:38,08
Oh, I'm so glad.

02:01:38,16 --> 02:01:42,75
It's a pity he can't marry her now. At least there'd be one less mouth to feed.

02:01:46,20 --> 02:01:47,72
Oh, another one.

02:01:48,30 --> 02:01:49,63
I hope this one isn't hungry.

02:01:49,70 --> 02:01:50,79
He'll be hungry.

02:01:50,87 --> 02:01:53,70
I'll tell Prissy to get an extra plate

02:02:05,15 --> 02:02:06,34
Ashley.

02:02:08,49 --> 02:02:09,75
Ashley.

02:02:11,46 --> 02:02:13,00
Darling.

02:02:22,84 --> 02:02:25,53
Miss Scarlett. Don't spoil it, Miss Scarlett.

02:02:25,60 --> 02:02:28,51
Turn me loose, you fool. Turn me loose, it's Ashley.

02:02:28,57 --> 02:02:30,67
He's her husband, ain't he?

02:02:42,89 --> 02:02:45,08
Miss Scarlett, ma'am. High time you got back.

02:02:45,16 --> 02:02:47,26
